AUDIO: 'like title of your book and outline. And then you would just grab the ID from that and stick it into this automation. Okay? Hope that makes sense. So, the first thing we do here is I like to condense the tropes templates. This is'

[03:31] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'more just a way of saving on tokens than anything else, cuz the tropes template that I have is massive. It\'s several thousand words long, and I don\'t necessarily want that template to overpower everything else'

[03:43] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'that I want to include in these prompts. It also increases costs and all of that. So, I have this really quick step to condense those into just a bulleted list of all the tropes so that we know what'

[03:55] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'the tropes are, but because the tropes are not a huge part of this process, it\'s okay in my mind to make sure that they\'re that they\'re referenced, but'

